comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: Can you try to disconnect the fan and then replug it back. If it doesn't work try to reset the unit by holding the reset/Ip report button for 15 seconds then release and check the kernel logs again for changes. If the issue is still there then your fan might be broken and the only solution is to replace it with new one.

comments.author: Setes
comments.body: Hello dear, i have replug fans, reset the asic and try with other fans but same error

comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: Quote from: Setes on June 11, 2022, 10:50:41 AMHello dear, i have replug fans, reset the asic and try with other fans but same errorIf still does not work try to reflash the firmware through SD Card. Download the SD card image from this link below- https://service.bitmain.com.cn/support/download?product=Flashing%20SD%20card%20with%20imageThen look for T15 SD card recovery image.zip and then extra the image and open the folder then copy all files inside the folder and paste it to SD card. Now after copying the image into the SD card turn off your unit and then put the SD card into the unit and then turn it on. Then wait for the led flashing to stop and remove the SD card after. You can follow the sample instruction from this video below- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6_4oxhVT6hg

comments.author: GFDhd
comments.body: The log shows that the fan lost. You replied that you reset the ASIC and tried other fan. BitMaxz recommends that you reflash the firmware, wondering if the fan has come back to work? Also, I was wondering if you have tried replacing the fan's cable or checking the fan's connector?
